First, different proportions of water containing solutions (vol%) of THF, 1,4-dioxane, acetone, DMF, DMSO, methanol and ethanol were prepared. Then the powder of R-CDs was added to the above solvents to prepare 5 mg/mL of solutions while sonicating for a few minutes. The fluorescence spectra were collected four times for each experiment. Accuracy (R

                           2
                        ) was calculated for considering the fitting efficiency. The relative standard deviation (RSD) values are used to evaluate the reliability of the developed sensing method by error bars. The limit of detection (LOD) is calculated by 3σ/s, where σ is the standard deviation of the blank sample and s is the slope of the curve in the linear response region.
